3
00:01:52,930 --> 00:01:55,720
The fin's been smashed!

4
00:02:00,770 --> 00:02:04,020
The nerve of that damn runt!

5
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:06,650
Is he trying to destroy the ship?!

6
00:02:06,650 --> 00:02:07,860
Gin!

7
00:02:07,860 --> 00:02:10,150
Blow Zeff's brains out!

8
00:02:11,820 --> 00:02:13,280
Do it already!

9
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:19,040
B-But the 100 meals
he gave us saved our lives!

10
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:22,830
Gin, you son of a bitch!

11
00:02:22,830 --> 00:02:23,620
Hey!

12
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:27,250
It's not as if I attacked
you guys or anything...

13
00:02:28,420 --> 00:02:30,090
I only broke the fin.

14
00:02:31,550 --> 00:02:34,550
Hey, Cabin Boy! What do
you think you're doing?!

15
00:02:34,550 --> 00:02:35,550
Sinking it.

16
00:02:35,550 --> 00:02:36,510
What?!

17
00:02:37,970 --> 00:02:39,470
I'm gonna sink this ship.

18
00:02:42,350 --> 00:02:45,270
– That ain't funny!
– That ain't funny!

19
00:02:45,270 --> 00:02:47,900
So that's your explanation?!

20
00:02:47,900 --> 00:02:49,400
Are you crazy?!

21
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:52,780
If I destroy the ship, there'll be
no reason for them to attack.

22
00:02:52,780 --> 00:02:54,200
What?!

23
00:02:55,700 --> 00:02:57,990
What do you know?

24
00:02:57,990 --> 00:02:59,910
The kindness he's shown me...

25
00:02:59,910 --> 00:03:01,700
What do you know about this place?!

26
00:03:02,450 --> 00:03:04,660
You're gonna die for this restaurant?

27
00:03:04,660 --> 00:03:06,500
Are you stupid?

28
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:07,630
What'd you say?!

29
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,130
Dying isn't...

30
00:03:10,040 --> 00:03:12,510
Dying isn't how you
repay kindness!

31
00:03:13,210 --> 00:03:15,800
That's not what he saved you for!

32
00:03:16,470 --> 00:03:19,470
Being given life
and then dying anyway...

33
00:03:19,470 --> 00:03:21,430
means you're weak!

34
00:03:21,430 --> 00:03:24,430
Then what else can
I do to resolve this?!

35
00:03:27,270 --> 00:03:29,060
Now, now, you guys...

36
00:03:29,060 --> 00:03:30,980
Stop fighting.

37
00:03:30,980 --> 00:03:33,860
It's disgraceful for you guys
to fight each other now.

38
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:38,410
Besides, you can't pull any more stunts
as long as we have our hostage.

39
00:03:38,780 --> 00:03:42,740
How unfortunate that you're
facing the Krieg Pirates.

40
00:03:43,490 --> 00:03:48,000
And now my fire pearls
will burn you to death!

41
00:04:01,050 --> 00:04:02,050
Gin!

42
00:04:02,050 --> 00:04:03,470
Why...

43
00:04:03,470 --> 00:04:06,060
Gin?

44
00:04:06,060 --> 00:04:07,810
Sorry, Pearl.

45
00:04:07,810 --> 00:04:09,020
Stay down for a bit...

46
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:14,440
Gin!

47
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:16,490
Are you betraying us?!

48
00:04:16,490 --> 00:04:18,950
I'm sorry, Don Krieg.

49
00:04:18,950 --> 00:04:22,620
He saved our lives.

50
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:25,790
I don't want him to die like this.

51
00:04:25,790 --> 00:04:27,410
At least...

52
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:31,790
At least let me bury him
with my own hands.

53
00:04:36,210 --> 00:04:38,590
Have you lost your mind,

54
00:04:38,590 --> 00:04:42,390
Pirate Fleet Commander?

55
00:04:43,010 --> 00:04:44,850
Pirate Fleet Commander?

56
00:04:45,350 --> 00:04:48,480
So he wasn't just some grunt?

57
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:53,110
He cracked that guy's shield...
That's some power...!

58
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:59,240
See? My plan to lure
him out worked great!

59
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,360
Liar!

60
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:03,120
You really were going to
break the ship, weren't you?!

61
00:05:03,530 --> 00:05:04,620
Sanji!

62
00:05:04,620 --> 00:05:05,580
What?!

63
00:05:05,580 --> 00:05:11,500
I hoped you'd leave here unharmed,
but it looks like I won't get my way.

64
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:13,250
Yeah, so it would seem.

65
00:05:13,250 --> 00:05:18,010
I'll at least set things
right by burying you...

66
00:05:18,010 --> 00:05:19,220
with my own two hands.

67
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:22,340
Thanks.

68
00:05:22,340 --> 00:05:23,680
You piece of shit.

69
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:26,010
You too, Straw Hat.

70
00:05:26,010 --> 00:05:27,010
Well...

71
00:05:27,010 --> 00:05:30,600
I won't lose against a wimp like you.

72
00:05:33,270 --> 00:05:34,690
You bastard!

73
00:05:34,690 --> 00:05:37,280
What did you just say
to our commander?!

74
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:40,700
"Piece of shit"?! "Wimp"?!
That's some big talk over there!

75
00:05:40,700 --> 00:05:44,450
We're the Krieg Pirates,
the strongest crew in the East Blue!

76
00:05:46,450 --> 00:05:49,450
Isn't that just because
you had the most pirates?

77
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:57,340
Oh, boy...

78
00:05:57,340 --> 00:05:58,880
You hit the nail on the head...

79
00:05:58,880 --> 00:05:59,840
So I was right.

80
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:01,170
Son of a bitch!

81
00:06:01,170 --> 00:06:03,840
I'm gonna kill you!

82
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:03,840
Don't mock us!

83
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:05,300
Back off!

84
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:06,930
Don Krieg!

85
00:06:06,930 --> 00:06:08,350
But...

86
00:06:08,850 --> 00:06:14,350
If you get upset when called weak,
it just proves you are weak.

87
00:06:15,520 --> 00:06:18,480
Only the outcome will
determine your strength.

88
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,820
You've got me.

89
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:22,780
Don't get so worked up!

90
00:06:22,780 --> 00:06:24,990
– Y-Yes, sir!
– Y-Yes, sir!

91
00:06:24,990 --> 00:06:26,120
Gin!

92
00:06:27,030 --> 00:06:29,950
Finishing off that cook
is your responsibility.

93
00:06:30,790 --> 00:06:34,920
I'll take care of that
hapless fool over there...

94
00:06:36,130 --> 00:06:38,920
Understood, Don Krieg.

95
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:43,130
Hey, brat!

96
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:51,720
I'll make you truly experience
the power that conquered the East Blue.

97
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:58,230
I'll teach you just how worthless
your so-called devil fruit actually is.

98
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:01,530
Blah, blah, blah...
You talk too much.

99
00:07:01,530 --> 00:07:03,610
I'll kick your ass.

100
00:07:03,610 --> 00:07:05,150
It's that simple.

101
00:07:05,150 --> 00:07:07,410
I'm coming over now!

102
00:07:07,950 --> 00:07:10,030
Get ready for a thrashing!

103
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:12,370
Impudent brat.

104
00:07:14,370 --> 00:07:16,370
That chef is cooked.

105
00:07:16,370 --> 00:07:17,750
No kidding.

106
00:07:17,750 --> 00:07:21,840
When Gin uses that weapon,
it means he's serious.

107
00:07:29,350 --> 00:07:31,260
His nickname is...

108
00:07:31,260 --> 00:07:32,350
Hellspawn.

109
00:07:33,350 --> 00:07:35,690
No matter how much his enemy cries or screams,

110
00:07:35,690 --> 00:07:37,940
he mercilessly tortures them to death.

111
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:41,400
He's a demon without
a shred of sympathy...

112
00:07:45,490 --> 00:07:49,950
I'm sorry, Sanji,
but you can't defeat me.

113
00:07:49,950 --> 00:07:52,910
Just keep saying that, small fry.

114
00:07:58,500 --> 00:07:59,460
Here I come!

115
00:08:14,310 --> 00:08:15,430
You son of a...

116
00:08:23,020 --> 00:08:23,980
Sanji!

117
00:08:32,070 --> 00:08:33,240
So long...

118
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:37,040
Now, get lost already!

119
00:08:42,250 --> 00:08:44,130
Yeah! The commander is incredible!

120
00:08:44,130 --> 00:08:46,210
Crush him, Gin!

121
00:08:46,210 --> 00:08:47,510
– Sanji!
– Sanji!

122
00:08:47,510 --> 00:08:49,180
Pull it together!

123
00:08:54,180 --> 00:08:55,510
Die!

124
00:09:20,290 --> 00:09:23,580
That cook landed a blow on Gin...

125
00:09:23,580 --> 00:09:27,250
Is Gin gonna lose, too...?

126
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:28,840
You fools...

127
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:34,220
You've seen what he can do
time and again, haven't you?

128
00:09:34,220 --> 00:09:38,310
Gin is a coolheaded demon
that has earned my trust.

129
00:09:38,310 --> 00:09:42,190
That's exactly why I appointed
him as your commander.

130
00:09:42,690 --> 00:09:45,310
He'll show his true colors soon.

131
00:09:50,110 --> 00:09:52,490
How do you think Sanji's holding up?

132
00:09:52,490 --> 00:09:54,240
Terribly, of course!

133
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:56,910
With this on top
of the shield guy's attacks,

134
00:09:56,910 --> 00:09:59,540
he's got at least five
or six broken ribs.

135
00:09:59,870 --> 00:10:01,870
Those skewered dumplings...

136
00:10:01,870 --> 00:10:04,540
aren't as good...

137
00:10:04,540 --> 00:10:06,040
as I thought.

138
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:10,880
Is that the best
the commander can do?

139
00:10:17,930 --> 00:10:20,100
What's he doing at a time like this?

140
00:10:21,980 --> 00:10:24,560
Alright! He's wide open
for an ass-kicking!

141
00:10:30,030 --> 00:10:31,530
Don't strain yourself.

142
00:10:46,830 --> 00:10:50,630
You bastard! Do you
want to fight me or not?!

143
00:10:50,630 --> 00:10:52,050
Fight you?

144
00:10:52,050 --> 00:10:54,430
I don't see the need.

145
00:10:54,430 --> 00:10:56,220
What's needed is a means to kill.

146
00:10:56,220 --> 00:10:57,800
That's all.

147
00:10:58,220 --> 00:11:01,470
That's a man's way
of showing force, boy.

148
00:11:02,060 --> 00:11:03,890
Remember it, you damn monkey!

149
00:11:03,890 --> 00:11:05,640
What?!

150
00:11:05,640 --> 00:11:07,940
Take a monkey lightly,
and you'll get scratched!

151
00:11:13,780 --> 00:11:14,950
Sanji!

152
00:11:24,210 --> 00:11:27,370
Woo-hoo! His bones have to be
shattered by now!

153
00:11:27,370 --> 00:11:29,170
Get him!

154
00:11:29,170 --> 00:11:32,170
Dammit! That shield guy
over-tenderized him!

155
00:11:32,170 --> 00:11:36,010
And he must have taken a dozen hits
from those iron balls.

156
00:11:40,010 --> 00:11:42,930
You really do whatever you want...

157
00:11:43,470 --> 00:11:45,100
you small fry!

158
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,980
Damn...

159
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:56,570
He's really strong...

160
00:12:00,030 --> 00:12:01,080
Time to end this!

161
00:12:02,160 --> 00:12:03,540
Don't struggle anymore.

162
00:12:07,290 --> 00:12:09,250
What was that?! Pity?

163
00:12:11,420 --> 00:12:13,210
Don't underestimate me!

164
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:15,840
Gin!

165
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:20,640
Sanji!

166
00:12:24,770 --> 00:12:25,640
Sanji!

167
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:30,940
Oh, no! He can't even bear the impact
from his own attacks anymore!

168
00:12:45,950 --> 00:12:47,540
– Alright!
– Alright!

169
00:12:47,540 --> 00:12:50,170
That's our Gin!

170
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:55,090
You...

171
00:12:55,670 --> 00:12:57,670
damn bastard...

172
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:26,540
I can't do it, Don Krieg!

173
00:13:28,620 --> 00:13:29,540
Gin...

174
00:13:30,710 --> 00:13:32,330
I can't...

175
00:13:33,540 --> 00:13:35,750
kill this man...

176
00:13:36,250 --> 00:13:38,630
What'd you say?!

177
00:13:38,630 --> 00:13:40,380
It was...

178
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:44,090
It... It was...

179
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:46,350
the first time for me...

180
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:52,730
I'm so ashamed.

181
00:13:53,980 --> 00:13:55,060
Sorry...

182
00:13:55,060 --> 00:13:56,570
Thank you...

183
00:13:56,570 --> 00:13:58,110
I thought I was gonna die.

184
00:13:58,110 --> 00:14:00,320
I thought I was done for.

185
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:03,450
Delicious...

186
00:14:03,450 --> 00:14:04,740
It's so delicious.

187
00:14:04,740 --> 00:14:09,160
I've never eaten food so delicious.

188
00:14:10,290 --> 00:14:12,120
It's damn tasty, isn't it?

189
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:20,300
Sorry.

190
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:24,050
You're gonna get in trouble for
giving me a free meal, aren't you?

191
00:14:24,050 --> 00:14:27,100
No proof, no trouble.

192
00:14:31,730 --> 00:14:34,600
No one had ever...

193
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:36,940
treated me so kindly before...

194
00:14:38,860 --> 00:14:40,690
So...

195
00:14:40,690 --> 00:14:43,820
I can't kill this man!

196
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:46,740
Come back any time!

197
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,410
I know...

198
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:53,210
I don't intend to betray you.

199
00:14:53,870 --> 00:14:57,750
I don't think what we've done
up until now is wrong, either...

200
00:14:58,250 --> 00:15:01,920
I still respect your power
and appreciate you as well.

201
00:15:03,130 --> 00:15:06,510
I was overjoyed when you
put your trust in my strength

202
00:15:06,510 --> 00:15:09,010
by appointing me as their commander.

203
00:15:09,010 --> 00:15:14,060
So I've followed your orders,
and that's not going to change...

204
00:15:15,140 --> 00:15:15,940
But...

205
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:17,310
But...

206
00:15:18,270 --> 00:15:21,020
He's the only person
I can't bring myself to kill!

207
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:26,320
Don Krieg...

208
00:15:26,780 --> 00:15:28,700
If the circumstances allow it...

209
00:15:30,450 --> 00:15:33,660
I'd like for us to spare
this ship... this restaurant.

210
00:15:34,620 --> 00:15:36,750
You son of a bitch!

211
00:15:36,750 --> 00:15:40,500
As if defying my orders wasn't enough,
now you're lecturing me?!

212
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:42,250
What's gotten into you?!

213
00:15:44,260 --> 00:15:46,970
How disappointing...

214
00:15:46,970 --> 00:15:52,310
There's nothing I detest more
than sympathy and morality.

215
00:15:53,100 --> 00:15:54,980
Haven't I always said that?

216
00:15:57,520 --> 00:16:00,110
Clear the way, men.

217
00:16:02,020 --> 00:16:03,480
Don! That's...

218
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:08,950
O-Oh no! MH5!

219
00:16:08,950 --> 00:16:11,410
That's the most deadly nerve gas!

220
00:16:11,410 --> 00:16:12,200
What?!

221
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:13,160
Nerve gas?!

222
00:16:14,330 --> 00:16:15,660
Put your masks on!

223
00:16:14,790 --> 00:16:16,370
Put your masks on!

224
00:16:15,660 --> 00:16:17,750
Hurry up!

225
00:16:16,370 --> 00:16:17,750
We'll die too!

226
00:16:17,750 --> 00:16:20,380
To use a weapon like that...

227
00:16:18,670 --> 00:16:20,380
That's despicable, you bastard!

228
00:16:20,380 --> 00:16:22,630
Do you know what'll
happen if you use that?!

229
00:16:23,050 --> 00:16:24,710
Stop whining, you idiots.

230
00:16:24,710 --> 00:16:27,380
None of that matters.

231
00:16:27,380 --> 00:16:29,640
This is a battle!

232
00:16:30,050 --> 00:16:32,640
Winning is the only objective.

233
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:35,600
Foul play? Fighting dirty?

234
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:37,600
There's no such thing!

235
00:16:38,270 --> 00:16:39,980
Might makes right.

236
00:16:39,980 --> 00:16:42,980
The ends will always
justify the means!

237
00:16:43,520 --> 00:16:46,150
So what if I'm using nerve gas?

238
00:16:46,150 --> 00:16:47,690
Victory is all that counts!

239
00:16:49,240 --> 00:16:51,490
That's power.

240
00:16:54,370 --> 00:16:55,910
What a rotten bastard...!

241
00:17:01,880 --> 00:17:05,170
Throw that gas mask away!

242
00:17:06,550 --> 00:17:09,590
You're no longer one of us.

243
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:12,300
Die!

244
00:17:19,390 --> 00:17:22,730
I won't let you shoot that nerve gas!

245
00:17:22,730 --> 00:17:25,690
Stop scuttling about, anchor boy!

246
00:17:38,750 --> 00:17:39,960
D-Dammit!

247
00:17:41,290 --> 00:17:42,500
Gin!

248
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:45,880
You don't have to listen to
what that wimp says!

249
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:48,960
I'm kicking his ass here and now!

250
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:52,880
Don't mock Don Krieg!

251
00:17:53,760 --> 00:17:56,390
He is unmatched.

252
00:17:56,390 --> 00:17:58,060
You can't defeat him.

253
00:17:58,600 --> 00:18:00,180
Come to your senses, you idiot!

254
00:18:00,810 --> 00:18:03,560
That man is trying to kill you!

255
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:05,360
I deserve it...

256
00:18:05,360 --> 00:18:08,480
since I couldn't fulfill my duty,

257
00:18:08,480 --> 00:18:11,860
having shamelessly lost to emotion...

258
00:18:12,360 --> 00:18:13,360
This is...

259
00:18:13,360 --> 00:18:15,200
This is a well-deserved punishment!

260
00:18:17,660 --> 00:18:18,410
Gin!

261
00:18:18,790 --> 00:18:20,910
Why... Why?

262
00:18:21,870 --> 00:18:24,750
So you show your pride at the end...

263
00:18:24,750 --> 00:18:26,880
But it's too late.

264
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:29,340
Die together with that cook!

265
00:18:30,300 --> 00:18:31,760
Nerve gas...

266
00:18:31,760 --> 00:18:32,550
M...

267
00:18:32,550 --> 00:18:33,510
H...

268
00:18:33,510 --> 00:18:34,430
5!

269
00:18:39,970 --> 00:18:41,430
Here it comes!

270
00:18:41,430 --> 00:18:42,890
Dive into the sea!

271
00:18:42,890 --> 00:18:44,350
Chef Zeff! Get inside!

272
00:18:48,230 --> 00:18:49,570
I'm borrowing these.

273
00:18:49,980 --> 00:18:51,070
Sanji! Gin!

274
00:18:51,070 --> 00:18:51,990
Use these!

275
00:18:51,990 --> 00:18:53,030
Cabin Boy!

276
00:18:53,860 --> 00:18:54,990
Now for mine!

277
00:18:54,990 --> 00:18:56,410
Wh-What?!

278
00:18:56,410 --> 00:18:58,450
Everyone dove into the sea!

279
00:19:07,330 --> 00:19:09,130
What do I do?! What do I do?!
What do I do?! What do I do?!

280
00:19:16,090 --> 00:19:16,800
This...

281
00:19:17,430 --> 00:19:18,970
is power.

282
00:19:33,860 --> 00:19:36,150
I... I'm saved...

283
00:19:36,150 --> 00:19:38,490
Good thing I found
that mask when I did...

284
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:47,000
Wh-What a crazy bastard...

285
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:49,500
I can't believe he used
nerve gas in battle...

286
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:51,880
H-He's a devil...

287
00:19:51,880 --> 00:19:55,130
Yeah, no human being
would do something like that!

288
00:20:08,350 --> 00:20:10,860
Are Sanji and the cabin boy okay?

289
00:20:10,860 --> 00:20:12,190
Not sure...

290
00:20:12,190 --> 00:20:14,860
Look! The poison mist is clearing up!

291
00:20:24,830 --> 00:20:25,790
Gin!

292
00:20:29,790 --> 00:20:31,250
Let go...

293
00:20:31,670 --> 00:20:33,130
Let go of the mask!

294
00:20:34,630 --> 00:20:35,590
Gin!

295
00:20:35,590 --> 00:20:36,920
Where's your mask?!

296
00:20:41,300 --> 00:20:42,640
Did you...

297
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:44,100
give me your mask?

298
00:20:45,220 --> 00:20:46,060
Gin!

299
00:20:48,390 --> 00:20:49,900
What an idiot.

300
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:54,110
That pain is the result of feeling
indebted over getting a bite to eat.

301
00:20:54,650 --> 00:20:58,820
Well, I guess idiots don't
learn until they die, huh?

302
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:04,330
Don...

303
00:21:04,330 --> 00:21:06,330
Don Krieg...

304
00:21:08,750 --> 00:21:09,750
Gin...

305
00:21:14,630 --> 00:21:17,050
Gin, it seems...

306
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:24,300
It seems like you picked
the wrong man to follow...

307
00:21:28,310 --> 00:21:30,810
You're actually sympathizing
with that scum?

308
00:21:30,810 --> 00:21:31,770
Scum?!

309
00:21:31,770 --> 00:21:33,360
That's right.

310
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:37,570
An idiot who loses sight of our goal
and can't follow my orders

311
00:21:37,570 --> 00:21:40,030
is worthless to me.

312
00:21:40,030 --> 00:21:43,280
There's no guarantee
he won't betray me again.

313
00:21:43,280 --> 00:21:46,240
It's love that drives me to put
him down now. Don't you see?

314
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:51,120
I... I never imagined the don would
actually kill the commander...

315
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:52,370
Th-That can't be true...

316
00:21:52,370 --> 00:21:54,000
There's no way he would!

317
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:56,000
Gin is his right-hand man!

318
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,340
That's right.

319
00:21:57,340 --> 00:22:01,720
No one has been more faithful
to the don than Gin!

320
00:22:02,380 --> 00:22:04,220
Even back then...

321
00:22:04,220 --> 00:22:09,980
When Fullbody and the Marines came
after us as we escaped the Grand Line...

322
00:22:09,980 --> 00:22:11,180
Yeah...

323
00:22:11,180 --> 00:22:15,900
He acted as a decoy all by himself,
pretending to be the don...

324
00:22:15,900 --> 00:22:19,900
He always risked his life
fighting for Don Krieg...

325
00:22:19,900 --> 00:22:22,900
I never imagined the don
would try to kill him...

326
00:22:26,660 --> 00:22:28,410
How evil...

327
00:22:28,410 --> 00:22:30,410
Patty! We have
an antidote, don't we?!

328
00:22:30,410 --> 00:22:34,830
Antidote? Well, we have
medicine for food poisoning.

329
00:22:34,830 --> 00:22:36,840
It doesn't matter! Just bring it here!

330
00:22:36,840 --> 00:22:38,420
Idiot!

331
00:22:38,420 --> 00:22:41,050
If you wanna save him,
put the mask on him right away!

332
00:22:41,050 --> 00:22:43,760
It should have some sort
of detoxifying effect!

333
00:22:43,760 --> 00:22:46,970
Let's get him to the second floor
and have him just breathe.

334
00:22:46,970 --> 00:22:50,560
If there's a chance to save him,
that's the only way!

335
00:22:50,560 --> 00:22:52,810
Hurry up, Patty and Carne!

336
00:22:52,810 --> 00:22:54,810
Alright already!

337
00:22:54,810 --> 00:22:56,400
Me too?!

338
00:22:58,270 --> 00:22:59,770
It's no use.

339
00:22:59,770 --> 00:23:02,610
He'll live for another hour at most.

340
00:23:04,780 --> 00:23:06,530
Don't you dare die, Gin.

341
00:23:08,990 --> 00:23:10,830
Don't let someone like him kill you!

342
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:14,460
Cling to life! Got that?!

343
00:23:14,460 --> 00:23:17,080
I'll kick his ass for you!

344
00:23:17,080 --> 00:23:18,790
D-Don't...

345
00:23:18,790 --> 00:23:20,380
You can't...

346
00:23:20,380 --> 00:23:22,710
defeat him...!

347
00:23:22,710 --> 00:23:23,720
Cool down!

348
00:23:23,720 --> 00:23:27,300
Attacking head-on would be playing
right into his hands. You'll die!

349
00:23:30,180 --> 00:23:31,260
I won't die.

350
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:34,560
Shoot me all you want!

351
00:23:34,560 --> 00:23:35,390
Hey!

352
00:23:35,390 --> 00:23:36,520
Such a fool...

353
00:23:36,520 --> 00:23:40,110
The easiest enemy to kill
is one who's in a frenzy.

354
00:23:40,900 --> 00:23:44,900
The sea is your hell, anchor boy.
You're heading toward...

355
00:23:45,860 --> 00:23:47,320
Here comes...

356
00:23:46,490 --> 00:23:47,320
Bombs!

357
00:23:47,320 --> 00:23:49,030
...your graveyard!

358
00:23:49,030 --> 00:23:50,830
My graveyard?!

359
00:23:55,750 --> 00:23:57,750
Oh, no! Get out of there, Cabin Boy!

360
00:24:00,380 --> 00:24:01,340
He got hit!

361
00:24:06,630 --> 00:24:08,430
He's dead.

362
00:24:09,050 --> 00:24:10,390
Cabin Boy...

363
00:24:14,680 --> 00:24:15,430
You little...

364
00:24:15,430 --> 00:24:17,890
Gum-Gum...

365
00:24:17,890 --> 00:24:19,100
Hit me...

366
00:24:19,770 --> 00:24:20,480
Here it comes!

367
00:24:20,860 --> 00:24:22,440
...if you dare!

368
00:24:22,440 --> 00:24:23,570
That's dirty!

369
00:24:27,030 --> 00:24:28,320
Pistol!

370
00:24:29,410 --> 00:24:31,070
What?!

371
00:24:47,260 --> 00:24:49,970
Don Krieg is down!

372
00:24:49,970 --> 00:24:52,050
What the hell is this guy?!

373
00:24:52,050 --> 00:24:54,310
He punched the don
through his spiked cape!

374
00:24:54,310 --> 00:24:56,270
Ouch...

375
00:24:59,100 --> 00:25:00,980
This is unreal...

376
00:25:00,980 --> 00:25:05,360
We've never seen the don
brought to his knees...

377
00:25:05,360 --> 00:25:07,280
He hit the don in his face!

378
00:25:07,280 --> 00:25:09,740
Right through his
Kenzanspike Mantle, too!

379
00:25:09,740 --> 00:25:12,700
C-Can you believe that?!

380
00:25:20,120 --> 00:25:21,710
Is this...

381
00:25:22,210 --> 00:25:24,130
my graveyard?

382
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:26,050
Or is it...

383
00:25:27,670 --> 00:25:28,970
yours?

384
00:25:32,180 --> 00:25:33,510
My...

385
00:25:35,470 --> 00:25:36,720
graveyard?!

386
00:25:39,520 --> 00:25:41,020
Don't think...

387
00:25:43,440 --> 00:25:45,820
you can send me
to my grave with this.

388
00:25:48,570 --> 00:25:51,610
I'm not gonna die here.

389
00:26:09,260 --> 00:26:11,630
He's unhinged...

390
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:19,220
You see idiots like that
every once in a while...

391
00:26:19,220 --> 00:26:24,270
ones who will fight to the death
once they've set their eyes on a target.

392
00:26:25,270 --> 00:26:26,610
Fight...

393
00:26:27,230 --> 00:26:28,650
to the death...

394
00:26:29,480 --> 00:26:32,860
You're in trouble if someone
like that becomes your enemy.

395
00:26:35,820 --> 00:26:37,830
But you know,

396
00:26:37,830 --> 00:26:40,950
win or lose,

397
00:26:40,950 --> 00:26:44,790
I like guys like him!
